2026-03-30T06:51:14.628Z JOY-0094 item.created "AI tool commands must run under AI member identity" [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-30T06:51:22.566Z JOY-0094 comment.added "Currently, Joy commands from AI tools (e.g. Claude Code) run under the git user identity (horst.schwarz@joydev.com) when no JOY_TOKEN is set. This means all comments, status changes, and item creation are attributed to the human in the event log, even though the AI performed them. The AI member identity (ai:claude@joy) is only used when explicitly authenticated via token. This breaks audit trail integrity -- the log should reflect who actually performed the action.\n\nNeeds design decision: should Joy auto-detect the AI tool context and use the AI member identity without requiring a token? Or should the /joy skill always authenticate first? Tension between frictionless solo use and correct attribution.\n\nPossible approach: once the first AI member is registered in project.yaml, Joy requires authentication for ALL members (human and AI). This makes identity unambiguous -- no more implicit git-user fallback. Solo projects without AI members remain frictionless.\n\nOpen question: should unauthenticated use be allowed at all once AI members exist? Without auth enforcement, nothing prevents an AI tool from acting under a human member's identity -- effectively impersonating them in the audit trail. On the other hand, forcing auth on all members may be too restrictive -- individual members should perhaps decide whether they allow AI tools to act in their name. This needs careful consideration." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-30T06:52:04.250Z JOY-0092 item.status_changed "new -> in-progress" [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-30T06:54:48.803Z JOY-0092 comment.added "Plan: (1) Add version header comment to rendered SKILL.md, setup.md, and joy-block in CLAUDE.md/QWEN.md/copilot-instructions.md. (2) Replace hash-based check_tool_files() with version extraction -- parse Generated by Joy X.Y.Z from files, compare against running binary version. (3) Add integration tests per JOY-0092 comment." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-30T07:01:06.041Z JOY-0092 comment.added "[x] Added version header to joy-block, SKILL.md, and all agent/prompt templates. [x] Extended render_joy_block and render_skill signatures with joy_version parameter. [x] Replaced hash-based check_tool_files with version extraction -- parses Generated by Joy X.Y.Z from first 5 lines. [x] Added extract_version function to ai_templates. [x] 9 integration tests for version extraction (roundtrip, mismatch, all render functions). [x] 37 ai_templates tests total, 203 tests overall, clippy clean." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
