2026-03-30T18:46:08.716Z JOY-009A comment.added "New command joy mode <ID> to inspect effective interaction levels per member per item. Flags: --mine (all statuses for caller), --member <id> (all statuses for a member), --status <status> (filter to a specific status). Combinable. Default (no flags): current status, all members. Output follows Joy UI standard: full-width header/footer, dimmed annotations. The AI uses joy mode <ID> --mine to determine how to interact. Resolves all four layers (project defaults, project overrides, personal preference, item override) clamped by max-mode. See ADR-025 for resolution logic." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
